This paper deals with the problem of selecting diverse and important items from a large set, which is a common problem in machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a new algorithm for selecting landmark points within a training dataset, which is relevant to kernel methods and low rank matrix approximations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the connection between Christoffel functions and leverage scores, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the connection between the proposed method and determinantal point processes (DPP), which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.AI.
